		</div>		
		<section class="the-problem pure-g"> 
			<div class="pure-u-1 pure-u-md-1-2">
				<div class="text">
					<p>
						By age three, poorer kids have heard 30 million fewer words than wealthier kids— a word-gap that stunts early brain growth.
						 That makes them more likely to drop out of school, have an unstable family, and remain in poverty for the rest of their lives. They’re set up to fail before they even start preschool. 
					</p>
					<p>
						Books are the most effective way to get families talking, but low-income parents are tired and over-stressed. And 3 billion parents just don’t have access to any books or Internet. 
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
